<subSubSection id="C3776556EDD038B4FC9AFCB9FB90FC72" pageId="641" pageNumber="642" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD038B4FC9AFCB9FB90FC72" blockId="641.[810,1452,683,2070]" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD038B4FC9AFCB9FC25FC50" bold="true" box="[863,992,887,913]" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name of the new species refers to its laterally compressed body.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EDD038B4FC9AFC75FBE5F835" pageId="641" pageNumber="642" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD038B4FC9AFC75FA84FB63" blockId="641.[810,1452,683,2070]" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD038B4FC9AFC75FBA5FC14" bold="true" box="[863,1120,955,981]" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Descriptionoffemale.</emphasis>
Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD038B4FB6BFC75FAE4FC17" box="[1198,1313,955,982]" captionStart="FIGURE 436" captionStartId="642.[136,245,1703,1729]" captionTargetBox="[183,1422,211,1683]" captionTargetId="figure-21@642.[136,1451,182,1688]" captionTargetPageId="642" captionText="FIGURE 436. Nodoscarus compressus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, mandible; G, maxillule; H, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, E, 0.02 mm; F–H, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592192/files/figure.png" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Fig. 436A</figureCitation>
) vermiform, slightly compressed laterally, smooth, almost straight, unsegmented. Bodylength 6.07 mm; dorsoventraldepth of body 0.98 mm in middle. Both anterior and posterior regions of body narrowing; anterior region slightly curved ventrally; posterior end of body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD038B4FB0DFBABFA86FB41" box="[1224,1347,1125,1152]" captionStart="FIGURE 436" captionStartId="642.[136,245,1703,1729]" captionTargetBox="[183,1422,211,1683]" captionTargetId="figure-21@642.[136,1451,182,1688]" captionTargetPageId="642" captionText="FIGURE 436. Nodoscarus compressus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, mandible; G, maxillule; H, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, E, 0.02 mm; F–H, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592192/files/figure.png" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Fig. 436B</figureCitation>
) weakly incised. No caudal rami or caudal setae present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD038B4FC9AFB64FCB1F9F8" blockId="641.[810,1452,683,2070]" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD038B4FC1DFB67FB96FB05" box="[984,1107,1193,1220]" captionStart="FIGURE 436" captionStartId="642.[136,245,1703,1729]" captionTargetBox="[183,1422,211,1683]" captionTargetId="figure-21@642.[136,1451,182,1688]" captionTargetPageId="642" captionText="FIGURE 436. Nodoscarus compressus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, mandible; G, maxillule; H, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, E, 0.02 mm; F–H, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592192/files/figure.png" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Fig. 436C</figureCitation>
) lobate, setulose. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD038B4FCF7FB05FC00FB27" box="[818,965,1227,1254]" captionStart="FIGURE 436" captionStartId="642.[136,245,1703,1729]" captionTargetBox="[183,1422,211,1683]" captionTargetId="figure-21@642.[136,1451,182,1688]" captionTargetPageId="642" captionText="FIGURE 436. Nodoscarus compressus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, mandible; G, maxillule; H, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, E, 0.02 mm; F–H, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592192/files/figure.png" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Fig. 436C, D</figureCitation>
) also lobate, muchwiderthanlong, surface ornamented with numerous fine setules, armed with 5 or 6 small setae at anterodistal corner (1 short, blunt and aesthetasc-like). Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD038B4FB97FAFFFB07FA8D" box="[1106,1218,1329,1356]" captionStart="FIGURE 436" captionStartId="642.[136,245,1703,1729]" captionTargetBox="[183,1422,211,1683]" captionTargetId="figure-21@642.[136,1451,182,1688]" captionTargetPageId="642" captionText="FIGURE 436. Nodoscarus compressus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, mandible; G, maxillule; H, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, E, 0.02 mm; F–H, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592192/files/figure.png" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Fig. 436E</figureCitation>
) stout, 2-segmented; first segment (coxobasis) unarmed; second segment (endopod) about 1.5 timeslongerthan wide (22×15 μm), about half as long as coxobasis: armed with 6 smallsetae (arranged as 2, 2, and 2) plus short, stout terminal claw, about half as long as endopod. Antenna, labrum, and first and second mouthparts positioned in indented pre-oral cavity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD038B4FC9AF98FFA6DF813" blockId="641.[810,1452,683,2070]" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">
Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD038B4FC00F98FFBF3F99D" box="[965,1078,1601,1628]" captionStart="FIGURE 436" captionStartId="642.[136,245,1703,1729]" captionTargetBox="[183,1422,211,1683]" captionTargetId="figure-21@642.[136,1451,182,1688]" captionTargetPageId="642" captionText="FIGURE 436. Nodoscarus compressus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, mandible; G, maxillule; H, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, E, 0.02 mm; F–H, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592192/files/figure.png" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Fig. 436C</figureCitation>
) large, unornamented, constricted at proximal third, gradually broadening in distal twothirds, with almost straight posterior margin. Three pairs of mouthparts retained (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD038B4FBF1F966FB6CF903" box="[1076,1193,1703,1730]" captionStart="FIGURE 436" captionStartId="642.[136,245,1703,1729]" captionTargetBox="[183,1422,211,1683]" captionTargetId="figure-21@642.[136,1451,182,1688]" captionTargetPageId="642" captionText="FIGURE 436. Nodoscarus compressus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, mandible; G, maxillule; H, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, E, 0.02 mm; F–H, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592192/files/figure.png" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Fig. 436C</figureCitation>
). Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD038B4FAF0F966FA61F903" box="[1333,1444,1703,1730]" captionStart="FIGURE 436" captionStartId="642.[136,245,1703,1729]" captionTargetBox="[183,1422,211,1683]" captionTargetId="figure-21@642.[136,1451,182,1688]" captionTargetPageId="642" captionText="FIGURE 436. Nodoscarus compressus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, mandible; G, maxillule; H, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, E, 0.02 mm; F–H, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592192/files/figure.png" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Fig. 436F</figureCitation>
) as unsegmented, digitiform lobe tipped with 1 naked seta. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD038B4FC61F922FBD3F8C6" box="[932,1046,1772,1799]" captionStart="FIGURE 436" captionStartId="642.[136,245,1703,1729]" captionTargetBox="[183,1422,211,1683]" captionTargetId="figure-21@642.[136,1451,182,1688]" captionTargetPageId="642" captionText="FIGURE 436. Nodoscarus compressus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, mandible; G, maxillule; H, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, E, 0.02 mm; F–H, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592192/files/figure.png" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Fig. 436G</figureCitation>
) as stout lobe, bearing 6 naked setae (2 subdistal and 4 distal). Maxilla (third mouthpart, 
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD038B4FA45F8C0FCADF88A" captionStart="FIGURE 436" captionStartId="642.[136,245,1703,1729]" captionTargetBox="[183,1422,211,1683]" captionTargetId="figure-21@642.[136,1451,182,1688]" captionTargetPageId="642" captionText="FIGURE 436. Nodoscarus compressus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, mandible; G, maxillule; H, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, E, 0.02 mm; F–H, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592192/files/figure.png" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Fig. 436H</figureCitation>
) positioned just posterior to pre-oral cavity (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD038B4FABAF8FEFCACF8AC" captionStart="FIGURE 436" captionStartId="642.[136,245,1703,1729]" captionTargetBox="[183,1422,211,1683]" captionTargetId="figure-21@642.[136,1451,182,1688]" captionTargetPageId="642" captionText="FIGURE 436. Nodoscarus compressus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, mandible; G, maxillule; H, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, E, 0.02 mm; F–H, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592192/files/figure.png" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Fig. 436C</figureCitation>
), as small lobe tipped with 2 subequal, naked setae. Post-oral swelling present between third pair of mouthparts (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD038B4FCF7F858FC63F870" box="[818,934,1942,1969]" captionStart="FIGURE 436" captionStartId="642.[136,245,1703,1729]" captionTargetBox="[183,1422,211,1683]" captionTargetId="figure-21@642.[136,1451,182,1688]" captionTargetPageId="642" captionText="FIGURE 436. Nodoscarus compressus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna; F, mandible; G, maxillule; H, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, E, 0.02 mm; F–H, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592192/files/figure.png" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Fig. 436C</figureCitation>
), directed anteriorly, covering posterior part of labrum, with rounded margin. Maxillipeds and legs absent
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD038B4FC9AF814FBE5F835" blockId="641.[810,1452,683,2070]" box="[863,1056,2010,2036]" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD038B4FC9AF814FC59F835" bold="true" box="[863,924,2010,2036]" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EDD038B7FC9AF832FF7CF7D7" lastPageId="642" lastPageNumber="643" pageId="641" pageNumber="642" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD038B7FC9AF832FF7CF7D7" blockId="641.[810,1452,683,2070]" lastBlockId="642.[136,778,1874,2070]" lastPageId="642" lastPageNumber="643" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD038B4FC9AF832FC09F7D7" bold="true" box="[863,972,2044,2070]" pageId="641" pageNumber="642">Remarks</emphasis>
. The unique numbers of setae on the mandible, maxillule, and maxilla, which are 1, 6, and 2, respectively, allow 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD338B7FE41F8BAFDEFF84C" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[388,554,1908,1933]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Nodoscarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="642" pageNumber="643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="compressus" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD338B7FE41F8BAFDEFF84C" box="[388,554,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="642" pageNumber="643">N. compressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EDD338B7FDF6F8BAFD2FF84F" box="[563,746,1908,1934]" pageId="642" pageNumber="643" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD338B7FDF6F8BAFD21F84F" bold="true" box="[563,740,1908,1934]" pageId="642" pageNumber="643">gen. etsp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
to be readily differentiated from its congeners. The slightly compressed body of the new species is also an unusual and characteristic feature of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD338B7FE1DF815FD45F835" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[472,640,2010,2036]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Nodoscarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="642" pageNumber="643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="compressus" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD338B7FE1DF815FE2EF835" box="[472,491,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="642" pageNumber="643">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD338B7FE3BF815FD45F835" box="[510,640,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="642" pageNumber="643">compressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD338B7FD4EF814FF7CF7D7" bold="true" pageId="642" pageNumber="643">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EDD338B7FD4EF814FF7CF7D7" pageId="642" pageNumber="643" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
